title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.1.1 MCH SYSTEMS AND POLICIES

description.narrative: Output 1.1.1 MCH Systems and Policies the Ministry of Health manage and monitor the provision and performance of quality and responsive priority life-saving health services for children and mothers from poor and vulnerable families, which contributes to Child Health, Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1.1 Equitable and Responsive Systems children and women have increased access to quality and responsive services, including social benefits

title.narrative: % of primary health care facilities managing cold chain system according to national standards
